# Convolios — Project Context

## What is this?
Convolios is a desktop app (Tauri 2 + React) that merges all messaging channels into one AI-enriched inbox, organized by Person, not by App.

## Read first
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` — **start here.** Codebase patterns section at the top defines how things are built. Full reference below it.
- `PLAN.md` — the master plan. Stack, data model, build phases, milestones.
- `README.md` — product overview and setup instructions.

## Stack
- **Shell:** Tauri 2 (Rust + React)
- **Frontend:** React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind v4 + shadcn/ui
- **State:** Zustand (@tauri-store/zustand for persistence)
- **Data fetching:** React Query v5 + LocalStorage persistence
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (magic link, deep link callback via `convolios://auth`)
- **DB:** Supabase (Postgres + pgvector + Realtime + Edge Functions)
- **Messaging API:** Unipile (WhatsApp, LinkedIn, Instagram, Telegram, Email)
- **AI:** Gemini 2.5 Flash (triage) + Gemini Embedding 2 (semantic search, planned)

## Current phase
**Phase 2 — Polish.** Core messaging works. Focus on UX quality, performance, and reliability. No new features without polishing existing ones first.

## Secrets
All secrets are in 1Password vault `P&Co — Convolios`. Use `op read` or `op inject` to access. NEVER hardcode secrets. Use `.env.local` (gitignored).

## Key decisions
- Single-user app — one Convolios account = one person, no multi-tenant
- Dark mode first, "financial terminal" aesthetic
- Never auto-send messages (ban risk) — AI drafts, human confirms
- Use industry-standard patterns (e.g. `column-reverse` for chat scroll, not custom JS)
- Abstract channel providers behind a `ChannelProvider` interface
- Study Discord, Slack, WhatsApp Web for UI/UX patterns before implementing

